===================================================
   Redberry - Symbolic Tensor Algebra System
===================================================

 Redberry  is an open source Java framework providing
 core functionality of computer algebra system focused
 on working with objects with indices (tensors).

 For information about latests releases, downloads and 
 example code please visit our site:
 
   homepage:     http://redberry.cc/
   repository:   https://bitbucket.org/redberry/redberry

 This program is a free software: you can redistribute it and/or
 modify it under the terms of the GNU General Public License v3 as
 published by the Free Software Foundation, either version 3 of the
 License, or (at your option) any later version. Full license text 
 you can find in COPYING file.


 Requirements
----------------------------------------

 JDK 7 or later (http://jdk7.java.net/download.html)
 
 To build cc.redberry from source Maven 2.2 or later required
 (http://maven.apache.org/).


 Depending on Redberry using maven
------------------------------------------

 To include latest version of Redberry in your Maven project just
 add this lines to your pom's dependency section:

 <dependency>
 	<groupId>cc.redberry</groupId>
 	<artifactId>core</artifactId>
 	<version>X.X.X</version>
 </dependency>

Here X.X.X - Redberry version you want to use.  

 Building Redberry from the source
-------------------------------------------
 To build Redberry from the source code you will need Mercurial 1.9.0
 or later (http://mercurial.selenic.com/) and Maven 2.2 of later
 (http://maven.apache.org/).
 To clone latest version of Redberry repository type in this command:
 
     hg clone https://bitbucket.org/redberry/redberry
	 
 Or you can download a package with source code from our bitbucket
 page.
 
 Use this command to build cc.redberry with all dependencies:
 
     mvn install
 
 Or this:
 
     mvn jar:jar
	 
 to build jar with cc.redberry only.
 
Working with Redberry repositorie
-------------------------------------------------------
 If you want to contribute and develop Redberry, first sing up bitbucket
 and pass to Redberry page. There you will find fork link - click it and 
 follow instructions. If you will develop some feature fill free to 
 contact authors and pull your module in main repositories.
 
 
